      "content": "but \"strategic disaster\" sounds pretty definitive. if the goal of foreign policy is to protect national interests and maintain order, doesn't that make the failure the primary takeaway? i feel like calling it a \"moral necessity\" almost handwaves away the fact that it actually made the world less safe and more chaotic. is there even a way to call it a success if the long-term result is just more radicalization and failed states?",
